Security Considerations
Multi-Tenancy & Isolation
Instance Scoping: All cache operations scoped by instance_id
python
cache_key = f"{instance_id}:{conversation_id}_skills"
User Permissions: ServiceNow enforces ACLs on tool execution
Tools only access data the logged-in user can see
Example: Request Status Agent only shows user's own tickets
Token Expiration: JWT tokens have TTL and expire automatically
No Credential Storage: Agent orchestrator doesn't store user passwords
Uses token_hashcode as session identifier
Actual authentication handled by ServiceNow/CS
Summary
Authentication Method: Token-based (token_hashcode) + JWT for Mosaic + Basic Auth for ServiceNow

User Context Flow:

User logs in → CS creates session with token_hashcode
Request includes token_hashcode + instance_id
Stored in request context (thread-local)
Used for JWT token fetching (Mosaic calls)
ServiceNow tool execution uses Basic Auth but operates in user's context
All operations scoped by instance_id for multi-tenancy
Key Point: The token_hashcode acts as the primary user session identifier throughout the agent orchestrator, enabling user-scoped operations while maintaining security through ServiceNow's ACL system.





